<body>
  <%- include('partials/site-header', { current: 'features' }) %>
  <main class="page-main">
    <section class="page-hero site-shell"><span class="eyebrow">Built for AI conversations</span><h1 class="page-title">A clean document layer for the chats worth keeping.</h1><p class="page-lede">Claude2PDF turns public AI conversations into readable, searchable documents without forcing every provider into the same visual noise.</p><div class="hero-actions"><a class="button-primary" href="/">Convert a conversation</a><a class="button-secondary" href="/how-it-works">See how it works</a></div></section>

    <section class="section site-shell"><div class="section-head"><p class="section-kicker">Supported platforms</p><h2 class="section-title">One workflow across public share formats.</h2><p class="section-copy">Claude2PDF automatically detects the provider from the URL and applies a dedicated parser for that platform.</p></div><div class="platform-row"><div class="platform-card"><strong>Claude</strong><span>claude.ai/share</span></div><div class="platform-card"><strong>ChatGPT</strong><span>chatgpt.com/share</span></div><div class="platform-card"><strong>Gemini</strong><span>gemini.google.com/share</span></div><div class="platform-card"><strong>Grok</strong><span>grok.com/share</span></div><div class="platform-card"><strong>Qwen</strong><span>chat.qwen.ai/s</span></div></div></section>

    <section class="section section--soft"><div class="site-shell"><div class="section-head"><p class="section-kicker">Core features</p><h2 class="section-title">Designed for clarity, not screenshots.</h2></div><div class="card-grid">
      <article class="info-card"><div class="card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M6 3h9l3 3v15H6z"/><path d="M15 3v4h4M9 11h6M9 15h6"/></svg></div><h2>Searchable PDF</h2><p>Text stays selectable and searchable because the document is rendered as structured HTML before your browser creates the PDF.</p></article>
      <article class="info-card"><div class="card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M4 5h16v14H4z"/><path d="M4 9h16M8 5v4"/></svg></div><h2>Clean preview</h2><p>Review the title, date and conversation before export, then open the full document when you need a closer inspection.</p></article>
      <article class="info-card"><div class="card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M5 4h14v16H5z"/><path d="M8 8h8M8 12h8M8 16h5"/></svg></div><h2>Formatting preservation</h2><p>Paragraphs, headings, emphasis, lists, links, tables, inline code and code blocks are kept when the provider exposes them in the public page.</p></article>
      <article class="info-card"><div class="card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M12 3 5 6v5c0 4.8 2.9 8.2 7 10 4.1-1.8 7-5.2 7-10V6l-7-3Z"/></svg></div><h2>Privacy-aware flow</h2><p>Public-page extraction is server-assisted, while parsing, preview and final PDF export happen in your browser. Conversation content is not intentionally persisted by the app.</p></article>
      <article class="info-card"><div class="card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M12 2v20M2 12h20"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="8"/></svg></div><h2>Provider detection</h2><p>Paste a valid public share URL. Claude2PDF identifies the network and selects the corresponding parser automatically.</p></article>
      <article class="info-card"><div class="card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><rect x="7" y="2" width="10" height="20" rx="2"/><path d="M10 18h4"/></svg></div><h2>Mobile-friendly UI</h2><p>The conversion flow, inline validation and document preview are built to work across desktop and modern mobile browsers.</p></article>
    </div></div></section>

    <section class="section site-shell"><div class="section-head"><p class="section-kicker">Honest limitations</p><h2 class="section-title">Public links in, document out.</h2><p class="section-copy">Claude2PDF does not log into provider accounts, bypass access controls or retrieve private chats. Source platforms can change their public-page markup, and media-heavy or interactive content may be simplified or omitted.</p></div><div class="callout"><div><h2>Looking for export and archive guides?</h2><p>The Tools hub contains focused guides for common Claude conversation workflows, with more providers planned.</p></div><a class="button-secondary" href="/tools">Browse tools</a></div></section>
  </main>
  <%- include('partials/site-footer') %>
</body></html>
